---
title: Crème Brûlée
servings: 6
tags:
  - french
  - dessert
---

Preheat #oven to 325°F. Bring a #kettle{} of water to a boil.

In a #medium saucepan{}, heat @heavy cream{2%cups} and @vanilla bean{1}(split, seeds scraped)
over medium heat until barely simmering, about ~{5%minutes}. Remove from heat.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk @egg yolks{6} and @granulated sugar{1/2%cup} until
pale and thick, about ~{2%minutes}.

Slowly pour the hot cream into the egg mixture, whisking constantly.
[- Tempering prevents scrambled eggs! -]

Strain through a #fine-mesh sieve{} into a #measuring cup{} with a pour spout.

Divide among 6 #ramekins{}. Place in a #baking dish{} and fill with boiling
water halfway up the sides of the ramekins.

Bake for ~{40-45%minutes} until set at edges but slightly jiggly in center.

Remove from water bath. Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate for at
least ~chill{4%hours} or up to 2 days.

Just before serving, sprinkle @superfine sugar{6%tsp}(1 per ramekin) evenly
over each custard. Caramelize with a #kitchen torch{} until golden and bubbly.

Let sit for ~{1%minute} to harden before serving.
